The scotch egg is a British dish consisting of a shelled, hard-boiled egg that is wrapped in sausage or minced meat. The egg is then covered in breadcrumbs and deep-fried or baked until crispy. They can be eaten hot or cold as a savoury snack. The name “Scotch” comes from the term scotched referring to the preparation method of coating something with breadcrumbs and frying it. INGREDIENTS INSTRUCTIONS Step 1 Pre-heat the oven to 175 degrees Celsius or heat oil in a deep-fryer to 190 degrees Celsius. Step 2 Place 4 eggs in a sufuria with water and bring to boil. Cover and let them sit for 10-12 minutes. Remove from hot water, cool, and peel. Step 3 In a bowl, beat the other 4 eggs. Flatten the ground sausage/ minced meat patty to surround the boiled eggs. Very lightly, flour the patty and coat it with the beaten egg. Step 4 Deep-fry until golden brown, ensuring each side is well cooked. Or Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes Step 5 Cut in half to cool down and serve on a bed of lettuce and sliced tomatoes for garnish.  Add mustard or mayonnaise if desired. Then serve hot or cold with a cold drink or beverage.